Bookplate
Business card? no. fuck that. 

Bookplates are delightfully anachronistic. Like an elevator with an accordian pull door or a. Moreover, bookplates are fundamentally personal. A bookplate doesn't make itself known until one has visited someone's home, picked the book off a shelf, and opened it's cover. 

Bookplates seemed to be popular up until about the late fifties, and then died off quickly. why?

